145
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:07,279
All right, let's get back to the episode.

146
00:09:07,279 --> 00:09:11,839
Okay, so let's go over some of the objections that people do have to LTDs.

147
00:09:11,839 --> 00:09:21,760
I posted about lifetime deals on X and someone wrote something along the lines of lifetime deals are just founder coping for a bad product.

148
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:22,800
What do you think about that?

149
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:32,000
>> So what I feel is actually LTD exposes bad products really faster because these LTD customers are going to give very brutal feedback to you.

150
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:35,839
So I don't feel like LTD is just a core for a bad product.

151
00:09:35,839 --> 00:09:36,160
>> Cool.

152
00:09:36,160 --> 00:09:37,200
I I mean I like that.

153
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:41,120
What if instead you just offer your product for free to get feedback?

154
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:41,600
>> What happens?

155
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:45,040
What I've realized is free users don't actually validate the your product.

156
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:48,320
They will just consume it and if something doesn't work, they will just ghost you.

157
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:54,160
But already customers because they have put real money into your business, they are going to give you good feedback.

158
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:57,600
So they are going to basically tell you what exactly is broken in your product.

159
00:09:57,600 --> 00:10:05,760
The other alternative that I've heard about is maybe you offer a really cheap yearly plan or maybe even you offer just one year of access to the product.

160
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:06,800
What do you think about that?

161
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:17,839
>> Yeah, I don't think like you will be able to attract that much attention through cheap annual plans and also at the same time I don't think you will be able to generate that much of a revenue with cheap plans because see like we had generated $65 in 3 days.

162
00:10:17,839 --> 00:10:22,160
I don't think like if we have launched like annual plan we would have generated that much amount of money.

163
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:26,079
Now also like if you think about it, Ltd buyers actually feel special.

164
00:10:26,079 --> 00:10:28,560
They got a deal nobody else will get in future.

165
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:32,720
So this sort of creates an urgency in FOMO that annual plans won't be able to match.

166
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:33,600
>> Okay, cool.

167
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:44,800
The last objection that I hear is that doing an LTD will kill your future long-term growth because you can't make any money from those people that you sold the LTDs too.

168
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:46,160
What do you think about that?

169
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,200
>> That's actually not true.

170
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:50,880
What I've realized is you uh in future you can actually upsell them.

171
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:58,000
So that is another thing which you can do and and also at the same time what I feel is you don't want to launch LTD for a long period of time.

172
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,800
So for example we launched LD only for 3 days.

173
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:08,560
So the very good way to ensure you're not overselling LTS is just limit the time frame and also limit the number of users you are going to like support.

174
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:10,720
So we limited that to 300 users.

175
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:20,720
So because we launched only for 3 days and and also like we we did lot of upselling to these LTD customers that actually helped us build our subscription business as well.

176
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:21,040
>> Okay.

177
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:21,519
Interesting.

178
00:11:21,519 --> 00:11:24,720
I mean on that note I would love to hear about the transition.

179
00:11:24,720 --> 00:11:32,560
I mean you went from LTD strategy uh that sort of kickstarted the business but then you transitioned it to uh subscription.

180
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:39,200
I think a lot of people watching would like to hear what worked for you in terms of that transition and what advice would you have for other people trying to do the same?

181
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:45,120
One of the biggest thing that we did just after launching LTD was we actually make sure our customers were happy.

182
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,680
So we were really obsessed with our LTD customers.

183
00:11:47,680 --> 00:11:54,480
We used to spend like one or two hours every day on intercom answering their question helping them through content creation.

184
00:11:54,480 --> 00:12:01,760
Like we sometimes used to help them manually and then used to convert those workflows into features inside supergrow.

185
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,519
So we did this for a couple of months.

186
00:12:03,519 --> 00:12:05,519
It actually helped us a lot in improving the product.

187
00:12:05,519 --> 00:12:12,720
We also added these tools called clarity and mix panel to really understand what these customers were doing.

188
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:17,279
So we used to basically see which feature set they are using, which feature set they are not using.

189
00:12:17,279 --> 00:12:22,399
We did this like for a couple of months but then we created this plan of launching our product on product.

190
00:12:22,399 --> 00:12:30,240
So what we did we actually launched it on product and we were able to become like product of the week in product and and actually gave us 50 customers also.

191
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:39,040
So one of the key things these LTD customers actually helped us uh make our product and launch better because they actually evangelized our product everywhere.

192
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:42,000
I was not the only person talking about my product that day.

193
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:51,839
We had like 10 to 15 really happy LTD customers who actually talked about us on LinkedIn on Twitter on product hunt and they also shared about our product

194
00:12:51,839 --> 00:12:54,720
on these platforms like WhatsApp groups and stuff.

195
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:56,560
Launching on LTD is not just for cash.

196
00:12:56,560 --> 00:13:04,160
It's for these purposes also like we were able to create 10 15 ambassadors for our product that actually helped us make our product product of the week.

197
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:13,600
>> I think that's super cool and I didn't think about it that way is that lifetime helps build community around your product which led to a really big product hunt launch.

198
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:14,399
That's super cool.

199
00:13:14,399 --> 00:13:16,079
Let's switch topics real quick.

200
00:13:16,079 --> 00:13:18,000
Uh I want to hear about tech stack.

